01:09:08.373 --> 01:09:10.375 line:90% position:50% align:center
“To the Governing Body:

01:09:11.293 --> 01:09:13.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Over the past five months,

01:09:13.295 --> 01:09:18.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we have ‘seen our Grand Instructor
with our own eyes.’

01:09:18.008 --> 01:09:21.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We journeyed through his Word
and now our hearts

01:09:21.344 --> 01:09:25.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
“are overflowing with love,
gratitude, and trust in him.

01:09:26.766 --> 01:09:29.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When we began our Gilead training,

01:09:29.185 --> 01:09:32.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we often viewed scriptures
as individual puzzle pieces

01:09:32.147 --> 01:09:35.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
“selected and applied to certain situations.

01:09:35.483 --> 01:09:39.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now we have experienced
how these pieces come together

01:09:39.613 --> 01:09:44.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to reveal a unified
and complete mosaic of Bible truth.

01:09:44.075 --> 01:09:46.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We thank you for the undeserved privilege

01:09:46.911 --> 01:09:50.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to dig deep into
and immerse ourselves in God’s Word.

01:09:52.125 --> 01:09:56.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We appreciate the time and energy
that you shared with our class.

01:09:56.504 --> 01:09:59.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We benefited not only from the lectures

01:09:59.341 --> 01:10:03.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but also from the attention
you dedicated to us afterwards.

01:10:03.553 --> 01:10:07.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We have been strengthened
and encouraged by your humility

01:10:07.432 --> 01:10:11.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and how you have cultivated
‘the mind of Christ.’

01:10:11.227 --> 01:10:14.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your deep love and respect
for Jehovah’s Word motivates us

01:10:14.648 --> 01:10:18.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to continue to build our own appreciation.

01:10:18.276 --> 01:10:23.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your self-sacrificing spirit
encourages us to imitate your example.

01:10:24.115 --> 01:10:27.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We are thankful that Jehovah
uses you as a means

01:10:27.118 --> 01:10:30.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to ‘instruct us about the good way
in which we should walk.’

01:10:32.290 --> 01:10:35.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We are grateful for our instructors.

01:10:35.502 --> 01:10:39.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They helped us to ‘peer into
the perfect law’ of God’s Word,

01:10:39.089 --> 01:10:43.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
“discern its principles,
and make personal application.

01:10:43.885 --> 01:10:46.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Enthusiasm for the Bible accounts
brought them to life

01:10:46.971 --> 01:10:51.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and helped get the words off the page
and into our minds and hearts.

01:10:51.935 --> 01:10:55.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Their dedication to the art of teaching
reinforced our desire

01:10:55.772 --> 01:10:57.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to give our all each and every day

01:10:57.774 --> 01:11:00.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that we could
fully benefit from the class.

01:11:01.277 --> 01:11:03.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We want to express our gratitude

01:11:03.822 --> 01:11:06.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to the entire Theocratic Schools Department

01:11:06.908 --> 01:11:09.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for their tireless efforts behind the scenes

01:11:09.119 --> 01:11:12.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to make our busy daily routine
as smooth as possible.

01:11:12.831 --> 01:11:16.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Additionally, we are grateful
to the U.S. Bethel family

01:11:16.876 --> 01:11:20.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for their hospitality and generosity.

01:11:20.797 --> 01:11:23.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
“They have shown us in a practical way
what it means

01:11:23.383 --> 01:11:25.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to show love and kindness to strangers.

01:11:26.761 --> 01:11:28.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Knowing that they demonstrate

01:11:28.763 --> 01:11:32.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
“this love to every class year after year

01:11:32.308 --> 01:11:35.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
“must certainly make
our heavenly Father smile.

01:11:35.729 --> 01:11:38.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your beautiful example touched our hearts!

01:11:40.483 --> 01:11:43.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As we depart for our assignments,

01:11:43.111 --> 01:11:45.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we have in mind David’s words:

01:11:45.780 --> 01:11:49.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Be courageous and strong and go to work.

01:11:49.451 --> 01:11:52.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Do not be afraid or be terrified,

01:11:52.036 --> 01:11:55.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for Jehovah God, my God, is with you.’

01:11:56.583 --> 01:12:00.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Thank you for this indescribable gift
of being trained

01:12:00.253 --> 01:12:04.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to help strengthen and stabilize
his people wherever we may serve.

01:12:04.841 --> 01:12:08.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your brothers, Class 157.”

01:12:10.180 --> 01:12:12.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has been accomplished.

01:12:12.182 --> 01:12:14.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re now graduates.

01:12:14.225 --> 01:12:16.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’re proud of you,

01:12:16.269 --> 01:12:19.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
not for the academic achievement that you’ve

01:12:19.731 --> 01:12:24.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
striven for during this class,
but the remarkable effect

01:12:24.611 --> 01:12:29.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the wisdom, the love that you’ve
developed during this divine education.

01:12:30.283 --> 01:12:33.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
We anticipate
the strengthening and stabilizing

01:12:33.411 --> 01:12:37.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
that you will do
in your respective branch territories.

01:12:38.750 --> 01:12:43.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in the introduction we discussed
the need for all of us to stay hungry.

01:12:43.296 --> 01:12:45.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what about staying thirsty?

01:12:45.423 --> 01:12:47.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s consider that for just a moment.

01:12:47.050 --> 01:12:49.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s discuss one thirst

01:12:49.219 --> 01:12:52.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we need to quench every single day.

01:12:52.597 --> 01:12:55.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
I invite you to open to Psalm 143

01:12:56.810 --> 01:12:59.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
and notice with me, please, verses 5 and 6

01:13:00.438 --> 01:13:02.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Psalm 143:5, 6.

01:13:02.649 --> 01:13:06.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
There David said:
“I remember the days of old;

01:13:06.653 --> 01:13:11.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I meditate on all your activity;
I eagerly ponder over the work of your hands.

01:13:11.699 --> 01:13:13.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I spread out my hands to you;

01:13:13.993 --> 01:13:18.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am like a parched land
that thirsts for you.”

01:13:19.582 --> 01:13:23.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
So David thirsted for Jehovah.

01:13:23.127 --> 01:13:26.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thirst for Jehovah
as a parched land thirsts for water.

01:13:26.631 --> 01:13:30.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
Water makes the land revive;
it makes it flourish.

01:13:30.426 --> 01:13:33.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
Like a dry, crusty riverbed in Africa

01:13:33.179 --> 01:13:38.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
is revived and flourishes when distant rains
come and saturate the soil,

01:13:38.142 --> 01:13:42.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
so we want to satisfy our thirst
for Jehovah on a daily basis.

01:13:42.355 --> 01:13:44.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
How?
How do we do that?

01:13:44.482 --> 01:13:48.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we want to continue to learn more
about our Father on a daily basis,

01:13:48.903 --> 01:13:50.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
digging into his Word.

01:13:50.947 --> 01:13:53.241 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hosea 6:3 says:

01:13:53.241 --> 01:13:56.160 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We will know, we will earnestly seek
to know Jehovah. . . .

01:13:56.160 --> 01:13:58.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will come to us like a pouring rain,

01:13:58.288 --> 01:14:02.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
like a spring rain that saturates the earth.”

01:14:03.459 --> 01:14:07.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even at Gilead, you have only learned
“the fringes of [Jehovah’s] ways.”

01:14:07.797 --> 01:14:10.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
So there’s so much more that’s available

01:14:10.425 --> 01:14:13.761 line:90% position:50% align:center
through the organization,
through Jehovah’s organization.

01:14:13.761 --> 01:14:16.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep thirsting, keep learning.

01:14:16.055 --> 01:14:17.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
So learn about Jehovah.

01:14:17.682 --> 01:14:22.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
Another thing:
Maintain a regular routine of prayer.

01:14:22.103 --> 01:14:27.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Pray constantly”
is what 1 Thessalonians 5:17 tells us.

01:14:27.025 --> 01:14:29.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
The study note says:

01:14:29.068 --> 01:14:32.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Paul was not expecting the Thessalonians
to pray at every moment.

01:14:32.447 --> 01:14:35.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
Rather, he was encouraging them
to have a prayerful attitude.”

01:14:35.825 --> 01:14:37.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
So thirst for Jehovah.

01:14:37.952 --> 01:14:41.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep your relationship with him close.

01:14:41.247 --> 01:14:43.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
Always look to Jehovah.

01:14:43.082 --> 01:14:46.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
And will Jehovah satisfy your thirst for him?

01:14:46.419 --> 01:14:48.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absolutely!

01:14:48.421 --> 01:14:51.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can learn something
from what occurred in Samson’s life.

01:14:51.925 --> 01:14:54.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s found in Judges chapter 15.

01:14:56.429 --> 01:14:58.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
And just as we had assurance earlier

01:14:58.514 --> 01:15:01.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will care
for your spiritual hunger

01:15:01.351 --> 01:15:03.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
he will care for your thirst as well.

01:15:03.353 --> 01:15:05.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
Judges chapter 15, interestingly,

01:15:05.605 --> 01:15:08.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
verses 17 through 19 describe Samson’s life.

01:15:11.486 --> 01:15:15.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
He had just experienced, as the verse says,

01:15:15.698 --> 01:15:17.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
that “Jehovah’s spirit empowered him.”

01:15:17.533 --> 01:15:19.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
He became absorbed
in a theocratic assignment,

01:15:19.911 --> 01:15:21.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
fighting Jehovah’s enemies the Philistines

01:15:21.913 --> 01:15:25.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
and “with the jawbone of a donkey”
killing a thousand Philistines.

01:15:25.583 --> 01:15:26.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then what?

01:15:26.668 --> 01:15:28.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 17 says: “When he finished speaking,

01:15:28.753 --> 01:15:32.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he threw the jawbone away
and called that place Ramath-lehi.

01:15:32.674 --> 01:15:34.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then he became very thirsty,

01:15:36.177 --> 01:15:38.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and he called on Jehovah and said:

01:15:38.179 --> 01:15:41.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘It was you who gave this great salvation
into the hand of your servant.

01:15:41.391 --> 01:15:45.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But now am I to die of thirst and fall
into the hands of the uncircumcised?’

01:15:46.521 --> 01:15:49.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So God split open a hollow that was in Lehi,

01:15:49.899 --> 01:15:52.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and water flowed from it.

01:15:52.360 --> 01:15:54.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When he drank,

01:15:54.362 --> 01:15:57.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
“his spirit returned and he revived.

01:15:57.991 --> 01:16:01.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
“That is why he named
the place En-hakkore,

01:16:01.285 --> 01:16:04.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
which is in Lehi to this day”

01:16:04.872 --> 01:16:06.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
—”En-hakkore,”

01:16:06.499 --> 01:16:10.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
where Jehovah split open a hollow
to satisfy Samson’s thirst,

01:16:10.378 --> 01:16:12.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
his spirit returned, and he revived.

01:16:12.839 --> 01:16:14.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what’s the point?

01:16:14.924 --> 01:16:18.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s no antitypical jawbone of a donkey.

01:16:18.344 --> 01:16:19.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

01:16:19.637 --> 01:16:22.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in future days you will certainly be busy

01:16:22.682 --> 01:16:27.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
in theocratic assignments,
just as Samson was.

01:16:27.437 --> 01:16:31.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be sure to return to En-hakkore regularly

01:16:31.733 --> 01:16:34.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
and revive your spirit
by drawing close to our God.

01:16:34.861 --> 01:16:37.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
He is a lifeline to your success.

01:16:38.865 --> 01:16:41.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stay hungry, and stay thirsty,

01:16:41.993 --> 01:16:45.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
dear Gilead graduates.

01:16:45.204 --> 01:16:47.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
For this Gilead graduation
and for any occasion

01:16:47.915 --> 01:16:49.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
of eating and drinking at Jehovah’s table,

01:16:49.917 --> 01:16:53.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
may our hearts’ sentiments
be those of the psalmist

01:16:53.171 --> 01:16:56.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Psalm 107:1, 9.

01:16:57.759 --> 01:17:00.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
There it says: “Give thanks to Jehovah,

01:17:00.386 --> 01:17:04.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
for he is good;
his loyal love endures forever.”

01:17:04.182 --> 01:17:07.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
That ties in with Brother Mark’s talk too.

01:17:07.268 --> 01:17:12.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 9 says:
“For he has satisfied the thirsty

01:17:12.315 --> 01:17:16.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
and filled the hungry with good things.”

01:17:16.486 --> 01:17:19.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
So all praise goes to Jehovah

01:17:19.072 --> 01:17:21.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
for his bounteous spiritual gifts to us.

01:17:21.699 --> 01:17:23.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, dear Gilead graduates,

01:17:23.534 --> 01:17:26.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
stay hungry for spiritual food
and for God’s righteousness.

01:17:26.954 --> 01:17:30.625 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stay thirsty for Jehovah on a daily basis,

01:17:30.625 --> 01:17:32.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he, our loving Father,

01:17:32.668 --> 01:17:36.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
will continue to fill you up
with an abundance of rich dishes.

01:17:36.506 --> 01:17:38.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
We love you all very much.

01:17:39.801 --> 01:17:42.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
How faith-strengthening and encouraging

01:17:42.845 --> 01:17:47.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
not only for the Gilead graduates
but for each of us!

01:17:47.350 --> 01:17:49.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
And there’s more!

01:17:49.352 --> 01:17:52.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the coming weeks,
look for additional talks

01:17:52.563 --> 01:17:56.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
from the graduation in the <i> JW Library  </i>app

01:17:56.067 --> 01:17:59.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in the Videos section on jw.org.

01:18:00.571 --> 01:18:04.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
For this month’s postcard,
we travel to the Netherlands.

01:18:06.744 --> 01:18:09.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Netherlands means “the lowlands,”

01:18:09.747 --> 01:18:14.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
a fitting name for a country with more than
a quarter of its land below sea level

01:18:14.627 --> 01:18:18.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
and nearly 20 percent reclaimed from the sea,

01:18:18.214 --> 01:18:19.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
lakes, and marshes.

01:18:19.966 --> 01:18:23.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
Iconic windmills
and wooden shoes are reminders

01:18:23.886 --> 01:18:27.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
that managing water is a way of life here.

01:18:28.766 --> 01:18:31.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
An ingenious system of dunes, dikes, pumps,

01:18:31.519 --> 01:18:34.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
and barriers protects against floods.

01:18:34.856 --> 01:18:38.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Life’s water” of Bible truth
started flowing into this land

01:18:38.901 --> 01:18:41.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the early 1900’s.

01:18:41.237 --> 01:18:43.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
By the beginning of World War II,

01:18:43.489 --> 01:18:46.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
there were
about 500 Jehovah’s Witnesses here.

01:18:47.535 --> 01:18:52.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
They suffered severe persecution
by the occupying Nazis.

01:18:52.290 --> 01:18:55.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over 300 of our brothers

01:18:55.126 --> 01:18:58.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
were deported to concentration camps.

01:18:58.004 --> 01:19:02.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sadly, more than 130 of them died.

01:19:03.259 --> 01:19:07.013 line:90% position:50% align:center
Despite these challenges,
with Jehovah’s help

01:19:07.013 --> 01:19:10.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the faithful stand
of our brothers and sisters,

01:19:10.683 --> 01:19:13.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
the preaching work accelerated.

01:19:13.895 --> 01:19:16.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
In August 1945,

01:19:16.564 --> 01:19:19.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the first convention held after the war,

01:19:19.817 --> 01:19:22.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
4,000 were in attendance.

01:19:22.820 --> 01:19:26.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, about 30,000 Witnesses

01:19:26.824 --> 01:19:28.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
zealously preach here.

01:19:28.993 --> 01:19:31.704 line:90% position:50% align:center
The number of regular and special pioneers

01:19:31.704 --> 01:19:34.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
increased a total of 36 percent

01:19:34.248 --> 01:19:36.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the last three years.

01:19:36.542 --> 01:19:40.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ll see bicycles
just about everywhere in the Netherlands.

01:19:40.880 --> 01:19:44.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nearly 30 percent of all journeys
are made by bicycle.

01:19:44.967 --> 01:19:49.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our brothers and sisters love
to engage in the ministry on two wheels.

01:19:50.306 --> 01:19:53.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
In a country known for its many waterways,

01:19:53.184 --> 01:19:56.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
publishers preach from boat to boat

01:19:56.187 --> 01:19:58.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
and from ship to ship,

01:19:58.314 --> 01:20:02.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as in Rotterdam,
which manages the biggest harbor in Europe.

01:20:03.694 --> 01:20:06.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
We end our visit in Leiden,

01:20:06.280 --> 01:20:09.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
a beautiful, historic city.

01:20:09.033 --> 01:20:12.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is where the famous
Dutch painter Rembrandt

01:20:12.036 --> 01:20:14.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
was born in 1606.

01:20:14.997 --> 01:20:19.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the two congregations
in Leiden is De Kooi.

01:20:19.669 --> 01:20:22.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their territory is close to the tulip fields,

01:20:22.588 --> 01:20:24.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
which bloom from April to May

01:20:24.840 --> 01:20:27.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
and attract millions of tourists every year.

01:20:27.843 --> 01:20:31.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
Traditional Dutch cuisine
is known for herring,

01:20:31.430 --> 01:20:34.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
pastries, and <i>stroopwafels,</i>

01:20:34.267 --> 01:20:39.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
a delicious treat made up
of two waffle cookies held together by syrup.

01:20:40.064 --> 01:20:42.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dutch cheeses are known throughout the world,

01:20:42.733 --> 01:20:46.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
including Edam and Gouda,

01:20:46.279 --> 01:20:49.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
named for the towns in which they originated.

01:20:49.198 --> 01:20:53.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many of the De Kooi Congregation’s
129 publishers

01:20:53.661 --> 01:20:56.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
visited the picturesque
Meerburgermolen windmill

01:20:56.872 --> 01:20:59.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
to send you their love and affection.

01:20:59.667 --> 01:21:03.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:21:03.296 --> 01:21:06.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting!

